<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1929] EOFException with FormattedMessage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1929</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/78:&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/78:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To pass FormattedMessage completely we should pass string values from argArray together with argArray.length.&lt;br/&gt;
For now there is such bug: on readObject it&apos;s InputStream brings length of stringArgs but there is no values in InputStream to read. So if length &amp;gt; 0 there will be EOFException while reading null value from InputStream.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The unit test without the fix yields:&lt;/p&gt;

